6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to liens, creating lien for certain
individuals on manufactured home; requiring absence
8 of agreement between certain persons; providing for
enforcement of lien; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 97.1 of Title 42, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 In the absence of any other agreement between the real property
17 owner and the owner of a manufactured home, any person, firm, or
18 corporation who allows an individual to use or occupy real property
19 in order to utilize a manufactured home shall have a lien for the
20 fair rental value with respect to such manufactured home if the
21 owner of the manufactured home does not exercise ownership or
22 control of the manufactured home for thirty (30) days or more. The
23 lien authorized by this act may be enforced in the same manner as
24 liens created by Section 97 of this title.
